I can't think of anything
better than a hot waterfall.

149
00:07:29,880 --> 00:07:30,800
Oh yeah.

150
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:33,600
Right again, Ayano.

151
00:07:33,600 --> 00:07:34,400
Wow.

152
00:07:34,400 --> 00:07:37,320
I can't think of anything that
could top a hot stone spa.

153
00:07:37,320 --> 00:07:38,520
For sure.

154
00:07:38,520 --> 00:07:42,080
I'm just gonna go ahead and
say everything here is awesome.

155
00:07:42,080 --> 00:07:43,520
Throw your worries away!

156
00:07:48,120 --> 00:07:50,400
Finally, some peace
and quiet all to myself.

157
00:07:55,680 --> 00:07:57,160
I brought you some sake.

158
00:07:57,160 --> 00:07:59,320
I thought it might help
with your relaxation.

159
00:07:59,320 --> 00:08:00,120
Thanks.

160
00:08:00,120 --> 00:08:01,440
Yeah, that should do the trick.

161
00:08:04,480 --> 00:08:05,760
Hey, Catherine.

162
00:08:05,760 --> 00:08:09,120
You're the last person I
was expecting to bump into.

163
00:08:09,120 --> 00:08:10,280
What do you
think you're doing?

164
00:08:10,280 --> 00:08:11,800
Get out of here right now.

165
00:08:11,800 --> 00:08:13,680
You must have missed the sign.

166
00:08:13,680 --> 00:08:16,440
It says "unisex bath."

167
00:08:16,440 --> 00:08:20,240
So it's for girls and guys?

168
00:08:20,240 --> 00:08:22,600
[SCREAMING]

169
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:26,560
That was an overreaction.

170
00:08:35,080 --> 00:08:36,880
OK, I just need to calm down.

171
00:08:36,880 --> 00:08:39,320
It was a little
surprising to see him.

172
00:08:39,320 --> 00:08:42,880
And it was even more surprising
to see so much of him.

173
00:08:42,880 --> 00:08:46,240
But it hardly seems proper that
they would have unisex baths.

174
00:08:46,240 --> 00:08:47,720
No matter how much
time I spend here,

175
00:08:47,720 --> 00:08:50,000
I learn something new about
this country every day.

176
00:08:55,040 --> 00:08:56,440
Is anybody else starving yet?

177
00:08:56,440 --> 00:08:59,480
Yeah, I think
it's time to eat.

178
00:08:59,480 --> 00:09:01,320
And we probably
shouldn't wait for Kazuma.

179
00:09:01,320 --> 00:09:02,680
Who knows what he's up to?

180
00:09:08,360 --> 00:09:09,840
I think I've been
in here long enough.

181
00:09:26,640 --> 00:09:29,600
Hey, old man.

182
00:09:29,600 --> 00:09:31,200
Kazuma.

183
00:09:31,200 --> 00:09:32,000
Huh.

184
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:34,200
So how long have you
been back from the dead?

185
00:09:34,200 --> 00:09:35,600
That's just wishful thinking.

186
00:09:35,600 --> 00:09:37,000
I was never dead.

187
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:37,920
Oh yeah, that's right.

188
00:09:37,920 --> 00:09:39,520
I forgot that
useless son of yours

189
00:09:39,520 --> 00:09:41,440
decided to let you
live after all.

190
00:09:41,440 --> 00:09:43,240
I just figured you were so
embarrassed that you would

191
00:09:43,240 --> 00:09:44,520
have killed yourself by now.

192
00:09:44,520 --> 00:09:47,680
You shouldn't flatter
yourself over a single victory.

193
00:09:47,680 --> 00:09:49,360
Your arrogance is
only gonna make

194
00:09:49,360 --> 00:09:50,920
it that much more
humiliating when

195
00:09:50,920 --> 00:09:52,480
I defeat you the next time.

196
00:09:52,480 --> 00:09:53,600
Oh, next, time?

197
00:09:53,600 --> 00:09:55,000
Well, if, you insist,
I'd be more than

198
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:56,760
happy to kick your ass again.

199
00:09:56,760 --> 00:09:57,640
You're a fool.

200
00:09:57,640 --> 00:09:59,040
If you really
wanna test how much

201
00:09:59,040 --> 00:10:00,360
luck you've got
left in you, then

202
00:10:00,360 --> 00:10:01,840
what are we waiting for, boy?

203
00:10:16,240 --> 00:10:17,680
Come on, is that all you've got?

204
00:10:17,680 --> 00:10:18,680
You're pathetic!

205
00:10:24,720 --> 00:10:26,120
Well, you've got
some pretty impressive

206
00:10:26,120 --> 00:10:28,080
moves for a senior citizen!

207
00:10:28,080 --> 00:10:29,880
It's too bad you
haven't made any progress

208
00:10:29,880 --> 00:10:33,840
since you were a child!

209
00:10:33,840 --> 00:10:34,640
Father?

210
00:10:34,640 --> 00:10:36,640
What is he doing here?

211
00:10:36,640 --> 00:10:39,160
I had a weird feeling
something bad was gonna happen,

212
00:10:39,160 --> 00:10:41,160
but I never thought
it was gonna be this.

213
00:10:41,160 --> 00:10:43,160
Didn't they already
settle this fight?

214
00:10:43,160 --> 00:10:44,640
They fought, but
they never settled it.

215
00:10:44,640 --> 00:10:48,640
I guess this is my father's
return match or something.

216
00:10:48,640 --> 00:10:50,640
Do you think maybe we
should try to stop this?

217
00:10:50,640 --> 00:10:52,160
Yeah, but I have no idea how.

218
00:10:52,160 --> 00:10:54,680
It'd be suicide to get in
between the two of them.

219
00:10:54,680 --> 00:10:58,040
But you're the only
one that can, Ren.

220
00:10:58,040 --> 00:11:00,200
Kazuma and Cousin
Genma care about you

221
00:11:00,200 --> 00:11:02,240
more than anything in the
world, and neither of them

222
00:11:02,240 --> 00:11:03,400
would hurt you.

223
00:11:03,400 --> 00:11:05,520
So they have to stop
fighting if you jump in there

224
00:11:05,520 --> 00:11:07,000
and tell them to knock it off.

225
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:08,920
But what if they
don't see me somehow?

226
00:11:08,920 --> 00:11:11,200
Well, it'll probably be
a quick and painless death.

227
00:11:11,200 --> 00:11:13,680
Yeah, that's not
exactly reassuring.

228
00:11:19,680 --> 00:11:21,120
Excuse me, Genma,
but your dinner's

229
00:11:21,120 --> 00:11:23,880
gonna get cold if
you keep this up.

230
00:11:23,880 --> 00:11:25,200
I don't wanna wait
all night to eat,

231
00:11:25,200 --> 00:11:26,880
so why don't you come up now?

232
00:11:26,880 --> 00:11:28,080
AYANO: Detective Tachibana?

233
00:11:28,080 --> 00:11:29,560
What are you doing here?

234
00:11:29,560 --> 00:11:33,760
I'm here with Genma
for a romantic getaway.

235
00:11:33,760 --> 00:11:35,840
Just so we're clear on
this, I could easily kill

236
00:11:35,840 --> 00:11:37,800
you any time I feel like it.

237
00:11:37,800 --> 00:11:38,720
But‐‐

238
00:11:38,720 --> 00:11:40,600
But if there's anything
you hate more than me,

239
00:11:40,600 --> 00:11:41,880
it's a cold meal.

240
00:11:41,880 --> 00:11:43,840
That meal just
saved your life.

241
00:11:43,840 --> 00:11:45,280
You mean yours.

242
00:11:45,280 --> 00:11:49,440
You won't be so lucky
the next time we meet.

243
00:11:49,440 --> 00:11:50,880
[CHUCKLING]

244
00:11:58,800 --> 00:12:00,120
I'm starving.

245
00:12:00,120 --> 00:12:02,480
How about we get some grub?

246
00:12:02,480 --> 00:12:04,360
How could I eat anything
after hearing that?

247
00:12:04,360 --> 00:12:06,280
Does this mean now we're
gonna have to start calling

248
00:12:06,280 --> 00:12:07,640
Detective Tachibana "Mom?"

249
00:12:07,640 --> 00:12:08,600
That's so gross.

250
00:12:08,600 --> 00:12:10,720
Why couldn't she
have just lied to us?

251
00:12:10,720 --> 00:12:11,560
Yeah, yeah.

252
00:12:11,560 --> 00:12:12,840
You're both scarred for life.

253
00:12:12,840 --> 00:12:13,800
Now, can we eat?

254
00:12:20,760 --> 00:12:23,480
Aw man, I'm stuffed.

255
00:12:23,480 --> 00:12:24,600
I still can't believe it.

256
00:12:24,600 --> 00:12:26,840
Father mentioned spa
therapy once before,

257
00:12:26,840 --> 00:12:29,400
but I had no idea
he'd be coming here.

258
00:12:29,400 --> 00:12:31,600
I guess it really is a
small world, isn't it?

259
00:12:31,600 --> 00:12:32,720
Yeah, too small.

260
00:12:32,720 --> 00:12:36,040
And when did that geezer get
discharged from the hospital?

261
00:12:36,040 --> 00:12:40,400
You know, Kazuma, do you think
that maybe you and dad could‐‐

262
00:12:40,400 --> 00:12:41,760
Don't even finish
that sentence.

263
00:12:44,600 --> 00:12:45,840
All right.

264
